question: 空き缶
sourceMnemonic: A <kanji>sky</kanji> <kanji>can</kanji> is a can that has nothing but sky in it. It's an <vocabulary>empty can</vocabulary>.
sourceReadingMnemonic: The reading for <ja>空き</ja> isn't one you've seen before. Remember how <ja>開く</ja> means "to open"? Well, this can is also open, because nothing is filling it. The readings are the same between the two, as well. <ja>開く</ja> and <ja>空く</ja>, though in this case it becomes the stem form: <ja>空き</ja>.
